<item>
            <title>[NET-685] FTPClient.connect() hangs without any timeout and response. It blocks the whole JVM</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NET-685</link>
                <project id="12310487" key="NET">Commons Net</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello Everybody,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;we implemented a multithread scheduler in order to run many FTP connections (one for each customer). We use these connections to upload /download files from/to remote servers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Inside the scheduler, we use a&#160;ScheduledThreadPoolExecutor to run our FTP connections (about 50). We run one thread (which instantiates an FTPClient object) for each FTP connection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sometimes, one of those connections tries to connect to the FTP server and the method&#160;FTPClient.connect() hangs without any timeout. No log. No server response.&lt;br/&gt;
 The connection is blocked as well as the whole JVM.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We needed to restart the service to fix the production.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We already checked the following points during the issue:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the server is reachable;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;No overlapping between run threads;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the virtual machine runs correctly;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Every other connection works correctly (FTPS, SFTP, CIFS, ...) so far.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;(Production logs attached)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PULL-REQUEST link:&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/commons-net/pull/51&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/commons-net/pull/51&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks in advance,&lt;br/&gt;
 Simone&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;OS:&lt;/b&gt; Debian 9&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Java Version:&lt;/b&gt; 1.8&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Scheduler:&lt;/b&gt;&#160;On made development using Spring-boot. Multithreading Environment using Runnable Class.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
